HEADWORD: Interjangle
<hw>In`ter*jan"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make a
dissonant, discordant noise one with another; to talk or chatter
noisily.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Daniel.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

